This paper deals with the study of equilibria and efficiency in auctions, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The specific auction being studied is the Generalized Second Price (GSP) auction, which is commonly used in online advertising, and thus could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of learning strategies and information asymmetries, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of bounds and algorithms, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
